The paper discusses the concept of artefacts in software engineering, which is a fundamental aspect of software development processes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also proposes a meta model for artefacts, which involves abstraction and refinement relations, indicating a focus on programming languages and formal methods, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also emphasizes the need for standardization and clear understanding of artefacts, which relates to the sub-category cs.CY (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of artefacts in software development tools and processes, which relates to the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
